WEBVTT

00:01.293 --> 00:03.545
If I told you to design me
an underground city,

00:03.629 --> 00:06.757
a city for 25,000 people,
what would you say?

00:06.840 --> 00:08.383
I'd tell you it's impossible.

00:08.467 --> 00:09.968
There's no amount of money
that would allow you

00:10.052 --> 00:11.887
to excavate a space so large.

00:11.970 --> 00:13.639
Build me my city!

00:13.722 --> 00:15.807
[helicopter whirring]

00:15.891 --> 00:18.227
[♪ tense music playing]

00:18.310 --> 00:19.520
You got the real stuff, Sam.

00:19.603 --> 00:22.314
My old man's still crushing me
with blows like,

00:22.397 --> 00:24.608
"You're a joke, you're Peter Lawford.
You're only in the band

00:24.691 --> 00:26.610
-because of who you're related to."
-[Sinatra] Jesus!

00:26.693 --> 00:27.903
[over recording]
You need to do what we discussed.

00:27.986 --> 00:30.447
Take them out. That's an order.

00:30.530 --> 00:33.200
[Cal Bradford] People need to know
that there are survivors,

00:33.283 --> 00:36.870
that their people could be alive up there,
and I'm gonna tell them the truth.

00:36.954 --> 00:37.955
No, you're not.

00:38.455 --> 00:40.415
If I wanted to make a mixtape,
is that possible?

00:41.124 --> 00:43.293
Straight ahead and up the stairs.

00:44.169 --> 00:47.047
[♪ tense, melodic music playing]

00:48.507 --> 00:51.510
I've been listening to her
and I've been watching,

00:51.593 --> 00:53.387
and I'm gonna take her down.

00:53.470 --> 00:54.471
-[gunfire]
-[people screaming]

00:57.474 --> 01:00.143
People are alive, and I believe
your wife is one of them.

01:00.227 --> 01:02.938
[Teri Rogers-Collins]
My name is Teri Rogers-Collins.

01:03.021 --> 01:05.148
I'm here with other survivors.

01:05.232 --> 01:07.025
[Sinatra] You might want
to check on your daughter.

01:08.360 --> 01:10.153
Jane! Oh, my God!

01:10.237 --> 01:12.906
All I can think to do
is hide from all of this.

01:12.990 --> 01:15.075
-Would you come with me?
-I got you.

01:15.158 --> 01:16.493
Okay.

01:16.577 --> 01:19.913
You will release my people and you
will find out who murdered the president

01:19.997 --> 01:22.749
if you ever wanna see
your daughter or your wife again.

01:23.333 --> 01:26.753
The DNA from Cal's murder
didn't match anyone in the bunker.

01:26.837 --> 01:29.840
It appears our killer
came from the outside.

01:29.923 --> 01:32.884
♪♪

01:35.637 --> 01:37.264
♪ Put a candle ♪

01:38.640 --> 01:41.685
♪ In the window ♪

01:41.768 --> 01:44.604
[♪ "Long as I Can See the Light"
by Ted Hawkins playing]

01:44.688 --> 01:49.651
♪ 'Cause I fear I've gotta move ♪

01:52.904 --> 01:56.241
♪ Though I'm going, going ♪

01:56.325 --> 01:58.785
♪ I'll be coming home soon ♪

02:00.704 --> 02:05.917
♪ Long as I can see the light ♪

02:06.793 --> 02:08.211
Build me my city!

02:08.754 --> 02:10.630
♪ Pack my bags ♪

02:10.714 --> 02:15.010
♪ And let's get moving ♪

02:16.803 --> 02:20.140
-♪ 'Cause I'm bound to drift a while... ♪
-[people chattering]

02:20.223 --> 02:22.392
Alright, boys, that's half-hour.

02:22.476 --> 02:26.897
Half of an hour, 30 minutes,
not 31, not 32, because...

02:26.980 --> 02:29.900
-[all] Every minute counts.
-That's right.

02:29.983 --> 02:31.193
-Hey, boss.
-Yeah.

02:31.276 --> 02:33.320
I decided what I'm gonna do
with the money from this gig.

02:33.403 --> 02:35.405
Oh, well, I'm guessing municipal bonds?

02:35.489 --> 02:37.574
[laughing] Nah.

02:37.658 --> 02:39.701
Gonna get me a pretty little thing
with a fat ass.

02:40.452 --> 02:41.703
That's an equally sound investment.

02:42.329 --> 02:44.206
Hey, Wakanda,
what you gonna do with the money?

02:45.165 --> 02:47.167
I'm going to send it
back home to my mother.

02:47.250 --> 02:49.294
-[worker 2] Oh, my God.
-[workers snickering]

02:49.378 --> 02:52.255
[worker 1] Now, I feel guilty for wanting
to spend it all on some ass.

02:52.339 --> 02:53.965
-[locker door clanking]
-[worker 2] Come on, let's go.

02:54.049 --> 02:56.927
-[people chattering]
-[worker coughing]

02:57.010 --> 02:59.054
[truck rumbling]

02:59.137 --> 03:01.473
[people chattering]

03:08.772 --> 03:12.317
That looks and smells so much better

03:12.401 --> 03:13.819
than whatever the hell this is.

03:17.364 --> 03:19.616
-Here.
-[laughing] Oh, you don't have to.

03:20.992 --> 03:21.993
Eat.

03:23.412 --> 03:26.873
I tried my best to make it
as my mother does, but, you know.

03:27.833 --> 03:28.834
The spices.

03:29.626 --> 03:31.461
They wouldn't let me bring the spices.

03:32.421 --> 03:33.422
Eat.

03:35.340 --> 03:37.175
I just grab one? [laughing]

03:37.259 --> 03:39.511
-[Adam] Wait, like this.
-[laughing]

03:39.594 --> 03:42.055
[people chattering]

03:47.436 --> 03:48.437
Oh, my God.

03:49.813 --> 03:52.732
Are you kidding me?
This is incredible, Adam.

03:53.442 --> 03:56.903
-Abdourahman.
-Abdour-ah-mom.

03:58.321 --> 04:00.949
Adam is fine.

04:01.032 --> 04:02.242
[Trent sighing]

04:04.703 --> 04:06.037
But thank you for trying.

04:08.915 --> 04:10.083
Yeah.

04:11.168 --> 04:12.210
Dip.

04:14.588 --> 04:18.592
[♪ soft orchestral music playing]

04:18.675 --> 04:21.511
[inaudible]

04:24.431 --> 04:26.266
[Adam] No way.

04:27.726 --> 04:30.270
[gasps] Where did you find this?

04:30.353 --> 04:33.148
[Trent]
I tried four West African food shops.

04:33.231 --> 04:36.234
[♪ soft music continues]

04:36.318 --> 04:37.319
Hey!

04:39.529 --> 04:42.616
[inaudible]

04:45.118 --> 04:46.536
I am floating.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.580
[Adam weeping]

04:51.041 --> 04:53.794
-Santé.
-Cheers.

04:53.877 --> 04:56.421
-[bottles clinking]
-To anywhere other than here.

04:56.505 --> 05:01.009
-[explosions booming]
-[♪ soft orchestral music playing]

05:13.438 --> 05:15.524
[steam hissing]

05:16.817 --> 05:19.903
♪♪

05:28.328 --> 05:30.080
[worker coughing]

05:32.040 --> 05:33.458
♪♪

05:33.542 --> 05:36.336
-Hey, man, you okay?
-[coughing]

05:49.766 --> 05:50.767
[Anders] What is this?

05:51.977 --> 05:53.353
It's arsenopyrite residue.

05:54.938 --> 05:58.149
-It's an iron arsenic sulfide.
-I know. I know what it is.

06:04.447 --> 06:05.740
Shit. [laughs]

06:07.659 --> 06:10.036
We gotta shut this all down.
We should be able to get everybody--

06:10.120 --> 06:12.080
Will this compromise
the integrity of the site?

06:13.748 --> 06:14.833
[scoffs]

06:15.876 --> 06:18.795
I mean, as you know, the sulfide
is only toxic during early excavation.

06:18.879 --> 06:22.757
So, if you're asking if the site
will eventually be safe, it will.

06:23.300 --> 06:26.011
But the people working it will not.

06:26.094 --> 06:29.055
They'll get sick, and then sicker.

06:29.139 --> 06:31.308
Mm, I get it, I know, okay.

06:33.768 --> 06:36.146
Look, we'll, uh, just send
the guys back to housing

06:36.229 --> 06:38.106
for the time being, okay?
Give everyone the night off.

06:38.189 --> 06:39.608
It'll be fine, I'll take care of it.

06:39.691 --> 06:41.484
-Yeah.
-Right? [chuckles]

06:41.568 --> 06:42.819
Yeah, okay.

06:43.320 --> 06:45.780
-[indistinct chatter]
-[construction vehicles rumbling]

06:50.368 --> 06:52.203
[door lock beeping]

06:52.287 --> 06:53.538
[door lock buzzing]

06:54.456 --> 06:55.957
[buzzing]

06:59.878 --> 07:01.671
-I'm the project manager.
-[door lock beeping]

07:01.755 --> 07:04.007
-It's not working.
-[security guard] I can't let you in, sir.

07:04.090 --> 07:05.759
I need to take your badge.

07:05.842 --> 07:08.845
-[Trent] What-- what is going on?
-I'm sorry, this-- it wasn't my call.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.221
Why are my guys back in the hole?

07:10.305 --> 07:12.098
They will wear masks
and we'll work around it.

07:12.182 --> 07:14.976
I promise, I'll do everything I can
to keep them safe.

07:15.060 --> 07:17.687
The excavation continues,
it-- it has to continue.

07:17.771 --> 07:20.190
We both know
this isn't a recycling facility.

07:21.733 --> 07:23.318
What are we really building here?

07:23.401 --> 07:24.944
-Shut up.
-[fence rattling]

07:26.821 --> 07:29.658
Listen, you don't wanna mess
with these people.

07:31.284 --> 07:34.162
They have intelligence
something is coming.

07:35.664 --> 07:37.040
Something catastrophic.

07:38.333 --> 07:41.503
Please, just forget about this job
and forget about these men.

07:41.586 --> 07:42.837
There's nothing you can do.

07:42.921 --> 07:45.131
-Anders, wait.
-There's nothing any of us can do.

07:45.674 --> 07:47.217
W-- Wait!

07:50.679 --> 07:53.765
[♪ gentle, melodic music playing]

07:56.810 --> 07:59.562
-[phone beeping]
-[Trent] Adam, I need you to pick up.

07:59.646 --> 08:02.232
Just-- You're not listening to me
about what's coming.

08:06.277 --> 08:10.407
♪ Put a candle in the window ♪

08:10.490 --> 08:12.867
-[phone beeping]
-[Trent] Adam, it's me again.

08:12.951 --> 08:17.205
I know you think I'm crazy,
but please, just call me back.

08:21.668 --> 08:23.670
♪ 'Cause I'm going ♪

08:23.753 --> 08:25.839
-[phone beeping]
-[Trent] You're not listening to me.

08:25.922 --> 08:27.841
Nobody is listening to me.

08:28.925 --> 08:31.261
Well they-- They will soon.

08:32.512 --> 08:34.097
You will all listen soon.

08:38.184 --> 08:43.189
♪ Long as I can see the light ♪

08:46.401 --> 08:50.030
-♪ Long as I can see the light ♪
-Weapon!

08:51.614 --> 08:53.575
-[gunshot]
-The world deserves to know!

08:53.658 --> 08:55.326
Everyone deserves to know!

08:55.410 --> 09:01.541
♪ Ooh ♪

09:07.756 --> 09:10.550
[Teri] [on recording] I'm looking
for my husband, Xavier Collins.

09:10.633 --> 09:12.594
My children, Presley and James.

09:12.677 --> 09:14.804
They were headed to a complex in Colorado.

09:14.888 --> 09:16.056
-[static crackling]
-Once again, my name

09:16.139 --> 09:18.141
is Teri Rogers-Collins.

09:18.224 --> 09:20.018
I'm here with other survivors.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.645
[Sinatra, voice muffled] You might want
to check on your daughter.

09:25.899 --> 09:28.985
[♪ soft, tense music playing]

09:34.115 --> 09:36.409
It's over. Let 'em go.

09:37.118 --> 09:39.162
-What the hell are you talking about?
-Sinatra didn't kill POTUS.

09:39.871 --> 09:42.791
The DNA came back from the crime scene,
and it doesn't match anyone down here,

09:43.416 --> 09:44.918
which means there was DNA on the president

09:45.001 --> 09:46.711
that belongs to someone
who either snuck in here

09:46.795 --> 09:48.838
or was here before we showed up.

09:48.922 --> 09:51.007
I need to find out who that is,
and I need to find 'em fast,

09:51.091 --> 09:52.342
and I need you to tell everyone

09:52.425 --> 09:54.219
to stand down. Give me your gun.

09:54.719 --> 09:56.596
Like hell, I'm gonna give you
my fucking gun.

09:56.679 --> 09:58.431
I need to go back to the crime scene.
Something got missed.

09:58.515 --> 10:00.934
Collins, Collins, listen. We did our jobs.

10:01.017 --> 10:03.228
No, Robinson,
you fucking missed something.

10:05.271 --> 10:08.775
Look, if the DNA doesn't match
anybody down here,

10:08.858 --> 10:10.819
we need to be looking at arrival day.

10:11.653 --> 10:14.072
Sure, do whatever you want.

10:15.532 --> 10:17.450
What the fuck does she have on you?

10:18.076 --> 10:19.536
My daughter.

10:21.496 --> 10:23.248
[Henry Baines]
My fellow citizens,

10:23.331 --> 10:26.376
obviously, we experienced some
unusual occurrences today.

10:26.960 --> 10:29.921
We want to assure you
that everyone is safe

10:30.505 --> 10:32.549
and order has been restored.

10:33.299 --> 10:36.302
You are in no danger, but law enforcement

10:36.386 --> 10:38.721
does need the space to do their jobs.

10:39.347 --> 10:44.185
Any confidential info on the tablet,
any remote server access, I want it gone.

10:44.269 --> 10:45.770
-[worker] All of it?
-All of it.

10:47.105 --> 10:50.024
[Jeremy Bradford] She said,
"I need you to keep her out there

10:50.108 --> 10:51.818
"until I can speak to the others.

10:52.318 --> 10:55.280
"They found someone, a survivor,

10:55.363 --> 10:56.906
and they know there are more."

10:56.990 --> 11:00.285
And yet, while things
are now under control,

11:00.368 --> 11:04.289
today's events have made it clear to us
that President Cal Bradford

11:04.372 --> 11:06.916
may have died as a result of foul play.

11:07.000 --> 11:10.044
[diners gasping and murmuring]

11:10.461 --> 11:13.715
Okay, I-I-I, I think you should slow down.

11:14.591 --> 11:15.758
You need a break.

11:17.594 --> 11:20.722
[whispering] Samantha.
Samantha, come here.

11:23.308 --> 11:24.809
Something has come undone here.

11:25.727 --> 11:26.895
Sam.

11:28.188 --> 11:30.398
You are coming undone. Let me help you.

11:30.481 --> 11:32.775
I don't think you should waste
any more time on me, Gabriela.

11:33.234 --> 11:34.402
I'm not who you think I am.

11:37.614 --> 11:39.073
I've done terrible things.

11:39.157 --> 11:42.327
I've done unspeakable, terrible things.

11:42.869 --> 11:44.078
Okay, well,
there's nothing that we can't--

11:44.162 --> 11:46.456
You're excused, Dr. Torabi.

11:51.002 --> 11:54.714
[Henry] For the time being, we are asking
that everyone remain indoors.

11:55.089 --> 11:58.259
Rest assured, justice will be served.

11:58.343 --> 12:00.887
Everything will be back to normal soon.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.725
Billy and I used to sit around,

12:05.808 --> 12:08.394
eat like shit all day
until our stomachs hurt.

12:11.689 --> 12:13.316
Sorry, I'm such a buzzkill.

12:14.067 --> 12:16.194
No, don't-- don't be sorry.

12:17.195 --> 12:20.406
Um, I should--
I should give you some space.

12:20.490 --> 12:21.824
No, no, stay.

12:22.533 --> 12:25.161
Please. Just a little longer.

12:26.704 --> 12:27.830
[softly] Okay.

12:29.123 --> 12:30.166
[phone buzzing]

12:33.127 --> 12:34.629
Excuse me. Sorry.

12:35.838 --> 12:37.173
This is Jane.

12:37.257 --> 12:38.841
[Sinatra] I know you're close
with Xavier Collins,

12:38.925 --> 12:41.344
but I need to know
you'll do what needs to be done.

12:41.427 --> 12:43.972
-What do you need me to do to him?
-[Sinatra] No, I'll handle Collins.

12:46.140 --> 12:48.685
But I am wrestling
with what to do about the girl.

12:50.103 --> 12:51.646
[clearing throat] She knows too much.

12:51.729 --> 12:53.690
She could point to you,
and that could point to me.

12:53.773 --> 12:56.234
I'm sure I'm just being paranoid, but I--

12:56.317 --> 12:58.444
-[Jane Driscoll] I'll handle it.
-No, no.

13:00.154 --> 13:03.241
What I'm saying is I just wanna make sure

13:03.324 --> 13:05.118
-that we keep the lid on--
-[Jane] Got it.

13:05.702 --> 13:08.037
I do have a question for you, though.

13:08.621 --> 13:12.041
As you know, the president had a bunch
of video games I enjoyed,

13:12.125 --> 13:13.668
particularly the Wii.

13:14.294 --> 13:16.587
And I was wondering, well,

13:17.213 --> 13:20.258
if that Wii could be available.

13:20.341 --> 13:22.969
You know? For me?

13:24.721 --> 13:26.973
-I'm sorry?
-[Jane] If I take care of all this stuff.

13:27.056 --> 13:28.182
Are you fucking insane?

13:30.018 --> 13:31.769
Just don't do anything to the girl.

13:31.853 --> 13:33.313
I think we should end
the conversation here.

13:33.396 --> 13:34.939
It will be better that way.

13:35.023 --> 13:36.399
-Excuse me?
-[disconnected line beeping]

13:36.482 --> 13:40.403
[♪ tense, melodic music playing]

13:40.486 --> 13:41.946
[birds chirping]

13:54.959 --> 13:56.252
[Cal] You're not wrong, Xavier.

13:57.003 --> 13:58.755
What's in here will definitely kill me.

13:59.338 --> 14:02.425
[♪ tense, orchestral music playing]

14:27.116 --> 14:30.203
♪♪

14:37.293 --> 14:39.712
[singing] ♪ Another day ♪

14:40.755 --> 14:44.217
♪ For you and me ♪
Listening party?

14:45.760 --> 14:47.929
♪ Another day ♪

14:49.180 --> 14:52.058
♪ For you and me ♪
Listening party?

14:52.141 --> 14:55.228
[♪ tense, orchestral music playing]

15:18.876 --> 15:21.003
[Cal] [over speakers]
Hey, kid. It's your dad.

15:21.712 --> 15:23.840
I came down to the library
to make you a mixtape,

15:24.632 --> 15:28.469
and, uh, bury a few national secrets
while I'm here.

15:34.225 --> 15:36.227
[Xavier Collins]
812092.

15:37.770 --> 15:40.815
812092.

15:44.110 --> 15:45.361
[knocking]

15:48.990 --> 15:50.241
I need your help.

15:51.033 --> 15:53.995
Sorry, I decided to start
getting frat-house drunk, so...

15:54.078 --> 15:57.290
Every resident was given a psych consult
shortly after moving in down here.

15:57.373 --> 16:00.543
I need the information
from those consults for these people.

16:01.586 --> 16:04.380
-What is this?
-It's a list of everybody who was flagged

16:04.463 --> 16:07.592
on arrival day-- wristband issues,
breakdowns, anything.

16:07.675 --> 16:10.469
I need to know who from that list
might not be who they say they are.

16:10.553 --> 16:14.015
Okay, look, I didn't personally interview
thousands of people, my team did.

16:14.098 --> 16:16.517
And those files are confidential.
[clicking tongue] Cheers.

16:20.021 --> 16:21.397
I'm done asking nicely.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.399
[Gabriela sighs]

16:23.482 --> 16:26.569
[♪ soft, tense music playing]

16:39.624 --> 16:42.793
Mm, what about Jordan E. Bennett?

16:45.296 --> 16:48.633
Um, no. No, he's-- he's legit.

16:48.716 --> 16:51.260
Suffers from severe PTSD,

16:51.344 --> 16:53.804
and hasn't left his neighborhood
in over two months.

16:56.390 --> 16:58.809
So, why are you getting day-drunk?

17:01.854 --> 17:02.897
Oh, I don't know.

17:03.731 --> 17:04.899
Um...

17:05.650 --> 17:10.363
It's possible that I have been
telling people for the last decade...

17:11.989 --> 17:13.616
that a monster isn't a monster.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.578
-Shit.
-Yeah.

17:23.668 --> 17:25.753
[keys clicking]

17:27.380 --> 17:29.382
-Hm.
-Hm, what?

17:29.966 --> 17:31.425
It's-- I mean, it-- it's silly.

17:31.509 --> 17:35.096
It's probably nothing,
just an error, maybe.

17:35.179 --> 17:36.180
Mm.

17:38.266 --> 17:39.767
Okay, no, no, no, wait, wait.

17:40.768 --> 17:43.396
If what's in this file is right,
then something--

17:43.479 --> 17:46.816
something is very wrong.

17:49.068 --> 17:52.154
[♪ soft, tense music playing]

17:59.453 --> 18:00.746
[phone buzzing]

18:02.123 --> 18:05.209
[♪ tense, orchestral music playing]

18:31.611 --> 18:35.281
♪♪

18:44.665 --> 18:45.666
Oh, here, sit a while.

18:47.293 --> 18:49.128
-You don't gotta ask me twice.
-[chuckles lightly]

18:50.212 --> 18:51.213
How have you been?

18:51.964 --> 18:53.716
The last few days have just been a bit--

18:53.799 --> 18:55.468
Insane? Yeah, no shit.

18:55.551 --> 18:56.886
This is my third plate of these today.

18:56.969 --> 18:58.929
Well, I mean, they're just so damn good.

18:59.013 --> 19:00.431
[Maggie laughing]

19:00.514 --> 19:02.058
You were pretty damn good, too.

19:03.267 --> 19:04.644
[gun clicking]

19:06.312 --> 19:08.230
Don't move a fucking inch.

19:10.983 --> 19:14.278
[♪ tense, orchestral music playing]

19:40.930 --> 19:43.432
Now, I don't know who the hell
you really are, but Maggie Davis...

19:44.392 --> 19:46.560
carried a fucking EpiPen with her
everywhere she went.

19:47.228 --> 19:50.773
A spoonful of this cashew cheese shit
would've knocked her on her ass.

19:54.402 --> 19:56.028
I'm almost relieved.

19:57.530 --> 19:59.782
♪♪

20:05.037 --> 20:08.165
I deserve everything
that happens to me, but just know...

20:19.301 --> 20:20.678
He made me do it.

20:28.394 --> 20:29.395
Who?

20:32.523 --> 20:34.233
-[thudding]
-[grunting]

20:37.319 --> 20:40.156
Sorry, bud. Wrong place, wrong time.

20:45.369 --> 20:47.121
-[Teri] Hello?
-[Xavier] Teri, it's me.

20:47.204 --> 20:48.581
[Teri] [distorted]
Oh my God. Where are you?

20:48.664 --> 20:51.041
-Where are you?
-[Teri] I didn't make it.

20:52.418 --> 20:55.129
Be a good father. Be a good father.

20:56.213 --> 20:57.882
Be a good father to them.

21:12.480 --> 21:14.023
You don't recognize me, do you?

21:15.566 --> 21:17.109
The-- the real me, that is.

21:19.820 --> 21:22.156
I always wondered if one of you would.

21:26.535 --> 21:27.870
Weapon!

21:27.953 --> 21:29.705
[gunshot]

21:29.789 --> 21:32.625
The world deserves to know!

21:32.708 --> 21:36.295
Everyone deserves to know!

21:43.594 --> 21:47.097
It's okay, it's okay.
Agent Collins, you're-- you're concussed.

21:47.181 --> 21:49.016
It's gonna take a few minutes.

21:50.184 --> 21:52.186
Lucky for you, we-- we have some time.

21:54.104 --> 21:55.689
It's a long story, after all.

21:56.565 --> 21:59.777
[phone ringing]

22:01.612 --> 22:04.156
-[Adam] Hello?
-[Trent] You answered.

22:04.240 --> 22:06.242
[Adam]
I answered to tell you to stop calling.

22:06.325 --> 22:08.160
Don't hang up. Don't hang up, please.

22:13.582 --> 22:14.708
Do you think it's luck

22:15.584 --> 22:18.879
that the worst prison in the country
is in Colorado?

22:20.297 --> 22:22.716
It's fate that I'm even here...

22:23.801 --> 22:26.720
so I can be close to the site
when the time comes,

22:26.804 --> 22:30.224
so we can be close,
we can survive whatever is coming.

22:30.808 --> 22:31.892
Adam...

22:33.435 --> 22:36.397
-Adam. Please.
-[Adam] I'm dying.

22:38.315 --> 22:39.316
I know.

22:41.402 --> 22:43.445
I know, but I'm trying to save you.

22:43.529 --> 22:45.948
[Adam]
There's no saving what's coming for me.

22:46.031 --> 22:48.576
There is. Adam, I can save you.

22:48.659 --> 22:50.202
-Don't hang--
-[phone line disconnecting]

22:50.286 --> 22:51.829
[receiver clunking]

22:53.205 --> 22:55.207
[crying] Adam!

22:58.419 --> 23:03.048
Most disturbingly, some reports
indicate the wave may be as high as...

23:03.132 --> 23:07.887
-[♪ melodic orchestral music playing]
-[prison inmates shouting]

23:09.972 --> 23:12.933
-[knife thudding]
-[prison guard grunting]

23:16.687 --> 23:19.690
[door lock buzzing]

23:19.773 --> 23:22.860
♪♪

23:31.035 --> 23:32.036
[grunts]

23:32.119 --> 23:34.204
[car horns honking]

23:37.750 --> 23:39.752
[honking continues]

23:43.047 --> 23:44.298
Identification, please.

23:45.341 --> 23:47.092
[honking continues]

23:51.764 --> 23:53.807
-Y'all headed to the arrival coordinates?
-Yes.

23:53.891 --> 23:56.644
Uh, we're local,
coming from just outside of Denver.

23:56.727 --> 23:59.563
I'm a librarian, I'm on a list.
I'm definitely on a list.

23:59.647 --> 24:02.566
Alright, I tell you what,
entrance is about a mile ahead,

24:02.650 --> 24:04.568
but there's a path to get to it on foot.
I'll show you.

24:04.652 --> 24:05.778
-Oh...
-Bless you, Officer.

24:05.861 --> 24:07.279
-Thank you. Thank you.
-Yeah.

24:09.490 --> 24:11.450
Just on up ahead here,
you'll be-- you'll be able to see it

24:11.533 --> 24:12.910
when we get around this bend, okay?

24:15.955 --> 24:18.082
Hey, this is kind of a dead-end.
Should we--

24:18.165 --> 24:19.959
-[couple shouting]
-[gunshots]

24:24.421 --> 24:26.006
[electric shaver buzzing]

24:33.847 --> 24:35.808
[car horns honking]

24:35.891 --> 24:37.851
[person] Hey, what the fuck is this?

24:37.935 --> 24:39.687
What the fuck-- yeah, you!
What the fuck are you doing?

24:43.857 --> 24:45.859
[Maggie sobbing]

24:50.447 --> 24:52.449
[Maggie sniffling]

24:57.121 --> 25:00.124
-Fuck off!
-I'm not judging.

25:00.207 --> 25:02.001
[people shouting, fighting]

25:02.084 --> 25:03.836
I've done nothing with my life.

25:05.045 --> 25:08.090
The world is ending
and the only thing I thought to do

25:08.173 --> 25:12.136
was come here so I could smoke
and eat junk food in my car

25:12.219 --> 25:15.597
without judgment, for once.

25:19.476 --> 25:22.229
I'm having a ball. [laughing]

25:22.312 --> 25:25.816
[♪ soft orchestral music playing]

25:33.782 --> 25:36.201
You might be the only person in the world

25:36.285 --> 25:38.996
who's in the right place
at the right time.

25:39.079 --> 25:40.914
♪♪

25:40.998 --> 25:43.792
[arrivals officer] Surrender all weapons
and prohibited items

25:43.876 --> 25:45.919
-at the designated areas!
-[arrivals officer 2] Eli Davis.

25:46.003 --> 25:48.047
-Margaret Davis, uh...
-[scanner buzzing]

25:48.130 --> 25:50.799
Can I see your wristband, sir?
Your wristband?

25:50.883 --> 25:52.051
I need to see your wristband.

25:52.134 --> 25:53.719
What happened to your wristband,
is it broken?

25:54.428 --> 25:56.346
-It broke.
-It-- How did it break?

25:56.430 --> 25:59.183
Okay, how did this happen, sir? Sir?

25:59.266 --> 26:01.727
Sir, I-- I have a long line. I just need--

26:01.810 --> 26:03.604
-Is something wrong with him?
-Hey, take a deep breath, breathe for me.

26:03.687 --> 26:04.855
-[hyperventilating]
-Do you need a paramedic, sir?

26:04.938 --> 26:06.315
It's okay, it's okay.
Where's your inhaler?

26:06.398 --> 26:07.733
-Sir, I need you to stay calm.
-Everybody--

26:07.816 --> 26:09.234
-Everybody's gone.
-I need you to calm down.

26:09.318 --> 26:11.361
-We-- we almost didn't make it.
-[overlapping chatter]

26:11.445 --> 26:14.531
Oh, my God, oh, my God, oh God, oh God!

26:14.615 --> 26:15.866
Just go! Just go!

26:18.869 --> 26:22.664
So, I got in, and I set about
to finish the job.

26:22.748 --> 26:27.044
But then, I don't know,
I-- I'm embarrassed to say it.

26:28.587 --> 26:30.005
I got comfortable here.

26:32.633 --> 26:33.884
And I started thinking I...

26:35.511 --> 26:37.221
I deserved to survive.

26:38.889 --> 26:40.849
To live, even.

26:42.851 --> 26:47.064
For Adam, and for everybody

26:47.147 --> 26:49.149
who built this place
who didn't get invited.

26:50.067 --> 26:52.069
I was willing to live out
my days down here,

26:52.569 --> 26:55.030
quietly, sadly...

26:56.073 --> 26:59.743
in this library that I loved.

27:02.788 --> 27:03.956
Until...

27:04.373 --> 27:05.582
Hello, there.

27:05.666 --> 27:08.544
Your Honor. [clears throat] I mean, not--
uh, not Your Honor.

27:09.753 --> 27:10.754
What is-- what is it?

27:10.838 --> 27:12.339
-Mr. President.
-Cal is fine.

27:12.422 --> 27:15.008
If I wanted to make a mixtape,
is that possible?

27:15.092 --> 27:18.095
Yes, uh, we have--
we have the music library.

27:18.178 --> 27:21.014
Thousands and thousands of albums
in various formats...

27:21.098 --> 27:23.392
[♪ soft, tense music playing]

27:23.475 --> 27:25.727
[Trent]
It all came flooding back to me.

27:27.729 --> 27:29.857
[worker coughing]

27:34.820 --> 27:37.489
And I knew I had to finish what I started.

27:43.871 --> 27:46.790
[♪ soft piano music playing]

27:55.382 --> 27:56.717
Call me when you're sober.

28:05.809 --> 28:07.394
Have I ever made you proud?

28:09.062 --> 28:11.607
You never did anything
I didn't do for you.

28:11.690 --> 28:14.776
[♪ soft piano music continues]

28:19.114 --> 28:21.533
I'll forgive you when I can sleep again.

28:22.868 --> 28:24.620
And I'll sleep again when you're dead.

28:27.205 --> 28:30.292
[♪ soft piano music continues]

28:46.183 --> 28:50.103
♪♪

29:29.476 --> 29:33.563
♪♪

30:01.049 --> 30:04.553
♪♪

30:26.491 --> 30:27.492
I'll leave you be.

30:31.913 --> 30:35.333
So, you can tell everyone
who did this and why.

30:36.084 --> 30:37.961
No, don't do this, man.

30:38.045 --> 30:40.964
Thank you for waking me up
from this stupor.

30:43.216 --> 30:44.217
And...

30:45.927 --> 30:49.014
-[patting book]
-Thank you for this.

30:49.097 --> 30:50.682
[scoffs]

30:50.766 --> 30:53.435
I-- I knew the way out,
I just didn't know how.

30:54.352 --> 30:57.522
And whatever's left of the world
deserves to know.

31:00.650 --> 31:02.027
Please don't leave me here.

31:03.111 --> 31:06.531
Hey, I need the book.
That book tells me where my wife is.

31:06.615 --> 31:08.533
I need the book to find her.

31:08.617 --> 31:10.744
I need the book to find her, and I...
[voice fading]

31:10.827 --> 31:12.913
[♪ soft piano music concludes]

31:16.374 --> 31:17.375
[grunting]

31:17.459 --> 31:19.920
-[door thudding]
-Who's there?

31:20.003 --> 31:21.463
-[Robinson] Collins?
-I'm here!

31:22.714 --> 31:24.007
Oh, shit.

31:24.091 --> 31:25.592
-Is he here?
-No, it's clear.

31:26.134 --> 31:27.385
-Can you get me outta here?
-Yeah.

31:28.720 --> 31:30.013
Fuck. [grunts]

31:30.597 --> 31:33.308
It was him. It's the librarian.

31:33.391 --> 31:35.185
-Yeah, we need to call it in.
-No.

31:35.811 --> 31:37.062
I know where he's headed.

31:39.189 --> 31:43.068
[♪ tense orchestral music playing]

32:10.971 --> 32:14.099
♪♪

32:22.774 --> 32:24.234
-On your right!
-[Robinson] I got him!

32:24.818 --> 32:26.444
-[Xavier] Don't move!
-Okay, okay.

32:27.320 --> 32:29.906
You got me. You got me.

32:29.990 --> 32:33.201
[♪ soft, tense music playing]

32:38.582 --> 32:40.625
-Hey wait, no, no, hey, stop!
-[Robinson] Whoa, whoa! Hey!

32:48.091 --> 32:50.177
They had a chance
to start over down here...

32:53.638 --> 32:55.015
to build a better world.

32:59.394 --> 33:01.271
Instead, they chose more of the same.

33:03.023 --> 33:05.567
Bloated houses for the privileged few.

33:06.443 --> 33:07.485
Guns.

33:08.111 --> 33:09.571
Made this place a prison.

33:10.989 --> 33:13.241
[scoffs] It's the American fuckin' dream.

33:18.997 --> 33:21.625
But there are bodies scattered
in the dirt down here.

33:23.376 --> 33:26.504
People need to know this place
is nothing more than a grave site.

33:30.091 --> 33:31.468
Now, it'll be mine too.

33:31.551 --> 33:33.637
-Okay, wait, hey, look, look.
-[Robinson] No, no, no, hey!

33:33.720 --> 33:35.347
I'm putting the gun down, okay?

33:39.601 --> 33:40.602
Paradise.

33:42.938 --> 33:46.524
What a fucking joke. [sobbing]

33:47.442 --> 33:49.361
[Xavier and Robinson] No!

33:49.444 --> 33:51.947
-[Trent thudding]
-[glass shattering]

33:52.030 --> 33:54.282
[wind whistling]

34:09.673 --> 34:10.882
She's expecting me.

34:14.552 --> 34:15.679
I'm not here to start anything.

34:23.561 --> 34:26.731
I found him. It was the librarian.

34:27.899 --> 34:29.818
Same man who tried
to assassinate the president

34:29.901 --> 34:30.986
on the White House lawn.

34:31.569 --> 34:34.698
-He was hiding here in plain sight.
-The librarian?

34:37.492 --> 34:38.493
How?

34:40.078 --> 34:41.329
It's a long story.

34:42.330 --> 34:44.457
But you'll have plenty of time
to figure it out,

34:44.541 --> 34:47.377
because his body is currently
splattered on top of someone's roof.

34:49.504 --> 34:51.047
Now, where the hell is my daughter?

34:52.007 --> 34:55.176
[♪ soft tense music playing]

34:59.222 --> 35:00.223
Okay.

35:01.266 --> 35:02.642
I'll ask you one more time.

35:04.436 --> 35:05.604
Where's my daughter?

35:10.817 --> 35:12.193
I'm sorry, Agent Collins.

35:16.865 --> 35:19.451
I never intended
for things to go this far.

35:29.377 --> 35:31.212
God forgive me. [sniffling]

35:33.006 --> 35:34.007
I...

35:37.927 --> 35:41.097
[Xavier sobbing]

35:46.019 --> 35:49.356
[♪ tense orchestral music playing]

35:59.949 --> 36:02.535
-[gunshots]
-[Sinatra gasping]

36:05.997 --> 36:07.248
[whimpers]

36:07.332 --> 36:08.875
[Xavier] [breathing heavily]
Okay.

36:12.796 --> 36:14.005
What did you do?

36:15.423 --> 36:16.758
What did you do?

36:17.884 --> 36:19.094
What the fuck did you do?

36:19.177 --> 36:20.178
-[gunshot]
-Oh!

36:24.516 --> 36:25.600
Presley's fine.

36:25.684 --> 36:27.769
[Sinatra gasping]

36:29.020 --> 36:30.355
Xavier, she's fine.

36:32.357 --> 36:34.901
I-- I found her. I had her.

36:36.069 --> 36:38.279
-She's okay?
-She's at home, she's safe.

36:38.363 --> 36:40.740
She's with Brooks and Rainey.
I put them at the door.

36:42.867 --> 36:45.870
[gasping, groaning]

36:50.417 --> 36:52.460
He was gonna blow your brains out.

36:53.837 --> 36:55.714
But you're no use to me if you're dead.

36:58.466 --> 37:00.885
A long recovery ahead of you.

37:03.763 --> 37:06.141
Probably should have just
let me have the Wii.

37:08.268 --> 37:12.605
-[♪ soft tense music playing]
-[Sinatra gasping]

37:15.650 --> 37:17.569
[brakes screeching]

37:25.160 --> 37:26.703
[Xavier] My kids. Where are my kids?

37:26.786 --> 37:28.747
Everyone's here.
They're good, they're all safe.

37:31.750 --> 37:33.626
-Dad!
-Oh, my God, Dad!

37:33.710 --> 37:36.796
[♪ soft, tense music playing]

37:41.926 --> 37:43.261
-Are you okay? Are you hurt?
-Yeah, Dad, I'm fine.

37:43.344 --> 37:44.804
I'm fine.

37:48.475 --> 37:51.561
[♪ soft orchestral music playing]

38:09.454 --> 38:10.747
Sinatra's down.

38:13.249 --> 38:14.501
For now.

38:15.919 --> 38:18.004
But there will be somebody else
to take her place.

38:22.467 --> 38:23.927
Good book he left you.

38:29.390 --> 38:33.144
I can't go out there,
not after everything that's happened.

38:33.228 --> 38:34.771
Collins, he's showing you the way.

38:36.231 --> 38:39.359
-He gave his life for it.
-I can't just--

38:39.442 --> 38:41.361
-[hand banging]
-It is not just about you.

38:43.029 --> 38:44.989
It is not just about your wife.

38:45.990 --> 38:48.201
We need to know what's out there.

38:49.786 --> 38:51.329
We need to know who's left.

38:53.748 --> 38:58.253
I would die before I ever let anything
happen to those kids.

39:13.184 --> 39:15.395
Is this real?

39:19.232 --> 39:21.150
I promised her I would keep you safe.

39:22.193 --> 39:23.194
And you have.

39:28.825 --> 39:30.535
But now, you need to bring her home.

39:37.125 --> 39:40.211
[♪ soft orchestral music playing]

39:48.928 --> 39:51.389
[Cal] [over speakers]
Hey kid. It's your dad.

39:52.140 --> 39:54.475
I came down to the library
to make you a mixtape,

39:55.143 --> 39:58.980
and, uh, bury a few national secrets
while I'm here.

40:00.398 --> 40:03.860
Now, I know, not everyone
appreciates this kind of music like I do.

40:03.943 --> 40:06.362
You've made that abundantly clear
over the years.

40:06.446 --> 40:10.199
But, hey, not everybody has the exquisite
taste that your old man does.

40:11.367 --> 40:13.328
You know, I've always believed...

40:14.704 --> 40:16.748
I've always believed
you are what you love.

40:16.831 --> 40:19.918
And you know what,
I really love this shit.

40:20.001 --> 40:22.295
I do. Yeah.

40:24.756 --> 40:26.716
Yeah, you are the things you love.

40:27.300 --> 40:28.593
[Cal sighs]

40:30.178 --> 40:31.888
[over headphones]
And if that's the case...

40:33.389 --> 40:34.933
then I am you, my boy.

40:37.518 --> 40:38.686
And I think you're me.

40:40.939 --> 40:42.065
And Jeremy...

40:43.608 --> 40:45.401
You don't like this world I built?

40:48.905 --> 40:50.031
Fix it.

